.TH "ps3_write_ctr" 9 "ps3_write_ctr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ps3_write_ctr \- Write counter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ps3_write_ctr
.BI "(u32 cpu "  ","
.BI "u32 ctr "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "ctr" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "val" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Write 16 or 32 bits depending on the current size of the counter.
Counters 4, 5, 6 & 7 are always 16 bit.
